---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="DGX Spark containers" description="vertexnova/gsplat-spark and vertexnova/aiml-spark container setup on NVIDIA DGX Spark GB10.">

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="page-hero">
      <span class="tag orange">Setup guide · Apr 2026</span>
      <h1>DGX Spark — container setup</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Building the VertexNova AI/ML container stack on the NVIDIA DGX Spark GB10 Grace Blackwell.
        Two containers: one for 3D Gaussian Splatting, one for general AI/ML work.
      </p>
      <div class="spec-row">
        <span class="spec-pill">DGX OS 7.4.0</span>
        <span class="spec-pill">CUDA 13.0.2</span>
        <span class="spec-pill">Driver 580.142</span>
        <span class="spec-pill">ARM64 aarch64</span>
        <span class="spec-pill">GB10 · SM 12.0</span>
        <span class="spec-pill">128GB unified memory</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tab-bar">
      <button class="tab active" data-tab="prereqs">Prerequisites</button>
      <button class="tab" data-tab="gsplat">vertexnova/gsplat-spark</button>
      <button class="tab" data-tab="aiml">vertexnova/aiml-spark</button>
      <button class="tab" data-tab="verify">Verify & use</button>
      <button class="tab" data-tab="summary">Summary</button>
    </div>

    <div id="prereqs" class="tab-content active">
      <h2>Prerequisites — do once after first boot</h2>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <span class="step-title">Disable swap</span>
          <span class="badge done">done once</span>
        </div>
        <p>DGX Spark uses unified memory — CPU and GPU share the same 128GB pool. With swap enabled, heavy GPU workloads trigger a death spiral: training fills memory → OS swaps to disk → machine freezes. Disabling swap turns a machine freeze into a clean job crash.</p>
        <pre><code># Comment out swap in fstab
sudo nano /etc/fstab
# Change: /swap.img  none  swap  sw  0  0
# To:   # /swap.img  none  swap  sw  0  0

# Apply immediately
sudo swapoff -a
swapon --show    # should print nothing</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <span class="step-title">Verify GPU access from Docker</span>
          <span class="badge done">done once</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>docker run --rm --gpus all \
  nvcr.io/nvidia/cuda:13.0.0-base-ubuntu24.04 nvidia-smi</code></pre>
        <div class="note info">Expected output: NVIDIA-SMI 580.142 · Driver 580.142 · CUDA 13.0 · GB10</div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <span class="step-title">Pull base image</span>
          <span class="badge done">done once</span>
        </div>
        <p>All containers build on NVIDIA's official PyTorch container — Blackwell-optimised, ARM64 native, CUDA 13, PyTorch 2.7.</p>
        <pre><code>docker pull nvcr.io/nvidia/pytorch:25.03-py3
# Size: 21.8GB — download once, reuse for all containers</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">4</span>
          <span class="step-title">Standard run flags</span>
          <span class="badge info">always use</span>
        </div>
        <p>These flags are required for every container on DGX Spark. Without <code>--ipc=host</code>, PyTorch shared memory is capped at 64MB and will crash during training.</p>
        <pre><code>docker run --gpus all -it \
  --name CONTAINER_NAME \
  --ipc=host \                 # shared memory — required for PyTorch
  --ulimit memlock=-1 \        # no memory lock limit
  --ulimit stack=67108864 \    # 64MB stack
  -v ~/workspace:/workspace \  # persist files
  -p 7007:7007 \               # nerfstudio viewer
  IMAGE_NAME bash</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">5</span>
          <span class="step-title">CUDA arch for GB10</span>
          <span class="badge warn">critical</span>
        </div>
        <p>The GB10 is compute capability SM 12.0. PyTorch 2.7 in the NVIDIA container does not recognise <code>12.1</code> — use <code>12.0</code> when building any CUDA extension from source.</p>
        <pre><code>export TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST="12.0"
# Set this before: pip install gsplat, any CUDA extension build</code></pre>
        <div class="note warn">⚠ Using 12.1 raises ValueError: Unknown CUDA arch. Use 12.0.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="gsplat" class="tab-content">
      <h2>vertexnova/gsplat-spark:v1</h2>
      <p class="tab-desc">3D Gaussian Splatting workspace — gsplat 1.5.3, PyTorch 2.7, ARM64 native.</p>

      <div class="pkg-grid">
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">PyTorch</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">2.7.0a0</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">NVIDIA build · pre-installed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">gsplat</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">1.5.3</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">built from source · SM 12.0</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">CUDA</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">13.0.2</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">pre-installed · SM 12.0</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">gdown</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">6.0.0</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">scene download utility</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <span class="step-title">Launch base container</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>docker run --gpus all -it \
  --name gsplat-build \
  --ipc=host \
  --ulimit memlock=-1 \
  --ulimit stack=67108864 \
  -v ~/workspace:/workspace \
  -p 7007:7007 \
  nvcr.io/nvidia/pytorch:25.03-py3 bash</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <span class="step-title">Verify GPU inside container</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>python3 -c "import torch; print(torch.cuda.get_device_name(0))"
# → NVIDIA GB10</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <span class="step-title">Install gsplat from source</span>
        </div>
        <p>Must build from source — no pre-compiled ARM64 + CUDA 13 wheel exists on PyPI. The <code>--no-build-isolation</code> flag prevents pip from trying to install a conflicting PyTorch version.</p>
        <pre><code>export TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST="12.0"

pip install git+https://github.com/nerfstudio-project/gsplat.git \
  --no-build-isolation

# Compilation takes 5-10 minutes — normal</code></pre>
        <div class="note warn">⚠ Do NOT use --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu130 — it will try to replace the NVIDIA PyTorch build and fail.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">4</span>
          <span class="step-title">Verify gsplat</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>python3 -c "import gsplat; print('gsplat OK', gsplat.__version__)"
# → gsplat OK 1.5.3</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">5</span>
          <span class="step-title">Exit and commit</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>exit

docker commit gsplat-build vertexnova/gsplat-spark:v1
docker images | grep vertexnova</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="aiml" class="tab-content">
      <h2>vertexnova/aiml-spark:v1</h2>
      <p class="tab-desc">General AI/ML workspace — computer vision, data science, 3D geometry, JupyterLab.</p>

      <div class="pkg-grid">
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">PyTorch</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">2.7.0a0</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">pre-installed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">OpenCV</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">4.10.0</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">headless build</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">NumPy</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">1.26.4</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">pre-installed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">pandas</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">2.2.3</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">pre-installed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">scikit-learn</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">1.6.1</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">pre-installed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">scikit-image</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">0.26.0</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">installed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">matplotlib</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">3.10.1</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">pre-installed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">seaborn</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">0.13.2</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">installed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">trimesh</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">4.12.1</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">3D mesh processing</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">plyfile</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">1.1.3</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">PLY / splat files</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">JupyterLab</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">latest</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">notebook interface</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pkg-card">
          <span class="pkg-name">imageio</span>
          <span class="pkg-ver">2.37.3</span>
          <span class="pkg-note">image I/O</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="note warn" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem">
        ⚠ Not installed: open3d (no ARM64 wheel), tensorflow-cpu (no Python 3.12 ARM64 wheel).
        TensorFlow can run in a dedicated container using an older Python version.
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <span class="step-title">Launch base container</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>docker run --gpus all -it \
  --name aiml-dev \
  --ipc=host \
  --ulimit memlock=-1 \
  --ulimit stack=67108864 \
  -v ~/workspace:/workspace \
  nvcr.io/nvidia/pytorch:25.03-py3 bash</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <span class="step-title">Stage 1 — computer vision</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>pip install \
  opencv-python-headless \
  scikit-image \
  imageio \
  Pillow</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <span class="step-title">Stage 2 — data science</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>pip install \
  seaborn \
  tqdm \
  rich
# pandas, matplotlib, scikit-learn, numpy already in base image</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">4</span>
          <span class="step-title">Stage 3 — 3D geometry</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>pip install trimesh plyfile
# open3d skipped — no ARM64 wheel available</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">5</span>
          <span class="step-title">Stage 4 — dev tools</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>pip install \
  jupyterlab \
  ipywidgets \
  gdown \
  python-dotenv \
  pyyaml \
  requests</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">6</span>
          <span class="step-title">Exit and commit</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>exit

docker commit aiml-dev vertexnova/aiml-spark:v1
docker images | grep vertexnova</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="verify" class="tab-content">
      <h2>Verify & launch containers</h2>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <span class="step-title">Health checks after every reboot</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code># 1. GPU driver OK
nvidia-smi

# 2. Docker GPU access OK
docker run --rm --gpus all \
  nvcr.io/nvidia/cuda:13.0.0-base-ubuntu24.04 nvidia-smi

# 3. Images intact
docker images | grep vertexnova

# 4. NemoClaw running
docker ps | grep openshell</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <span class="step-title">Launch gsplat container</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>docker run --gpus all -it \
  --name gsplat-dev \
  --ipc=host \
  --ulimit memlock=-1 \
  --ulimit stack=67108864 \
  -v ~/workspace:/workspace \
  -p 7007:7007 \
  vertexnova/gsplat-spark:v1 bash

# Inside — verify
python3 -c "import gsplat; print('gsplat', gsplat.__version__)"</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <span class="step-title">Launch AI/ML container</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>docker run --gpus all -it \
  --name aiml-dev \
  --ipc=host \
  --ulimit memlock=-1 \
  --ulimit stack=67108864 \
  -v ~/workspace:/workspace \
  -p 8888:8888 \
  vertexnova/aiml-spark:v1 bash

# Inside — verify everything
python3 -c "
import torch, cv2, numpy, pandas, trimesh, plyfile
print('torch:', torch.__version__, '| GPU:', torch.cuda.get_device_name(0))
print('opencv:', cv2.__version__)
print('trimesh:', trimesh.__version__)
print('ALL OK')
"</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">4</span>
          <span class="step-title">Launch JupyterLab</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code># Inside aiml-dev container
jupyter lab --ip=0.0.0.0 --port=8888 --no-browser --allow-root

# On your laptop browser
# http://dgx-spark.local:8888</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">5</span>
          <span class="step-title">Re-enter stopped container</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code># Check if stopped
docker ps -a | grep dev

# Restart and re-enter
docker start aiml-dev
docker exec -it aiml-dev bash

# Or one line
docker start -ai aiml-dev</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-header">
          <span class="step-num">6</span>
          <span class="step-title">Save work after install session</span>
        </div>
        <pre><code>exit
docker commit aiml-dev vertexnova/aiml-spark:v2
docker images | grep vertexnova</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="summary" class="tab-content">
      <h2>Container registry summary</h2>

      <div class="summary-grid">
        <div class="summary-card active-card">
          <div class="summary-header">
            <code class="summary-name">vertexnova/gsplat-spark</code>
            <span class="badge done">v1 built</span>
          </div>
          <p>3D Gaussian Splatting workspace.</p>
          <div class="summary-pkgs">
            <span class="tag">gsplat 1.5.3</span>
            <span class="tag">PyTorch 2.7</span>
            <span class="tag">CUDA 13</span>
            <span class="tag">ARM64</span>
            <span class="tag">gdown</span>
          </div>
          <div class="summary-size">21.9 GB</div>
        </div>

        <div class="summary-card active-card">
          <div class="summary-header">
            <code class="summary-name">vertexnova/aiml-spark</code>
            <span class="badge done">v1 built</span>
          </div>
          <p>General AI/ML workspace.</p>
          <div class="summary-pkgs">
            <span class="tag">PyTorch 2.7</span>
            <span class="tag">OpenCV 4.10</span>
            <span class="tag">trimesh</span>
            <span class="tag">plyfile</span>
            <span class="tag">JupyterLab</span>
            <span class="tag">pandas</span>
            <span class="tag">scikit-learn</span>
            <span class="tag">seaborn</span>
          </div>
          <div class="summary-size">22.0 GB</div>
        </div>

        <div class="summary-card planned-card">
          <div class="summary-header">
            <code class="summary-name">vertexnova/nerfstudio-spark</code>
            <span class="badge planned">planned</span>
          </div>
          <p>Full nerfstudio with COLMAP for training 3DGS from custom scenes.</p>
          <div class="summary-pkgs">
            <span class="tag">nerfstudio</span>
            <span class="tag">COLMAP</span>
            <span class="tag">gsplat</span>
            <span class="tag">Open3D</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="summary-card planned-card">
          <div class="summary-header">
            <code class="summary-name">vertexnova/vertexnova-spark</code>
            <span class="badge planned">planned</span>
          </div>
          <p>C++ rendering engine development — Vulkan, CMake, SPIRV-Cross.</p>
          <div class="summary-pkgs">
            <span class="tag">CMake</span>
            <span class="tag">Vulkan SDK</span>
            <span class="tag">SPIRV-Cross</span>
            <span class="tag">clang</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 style="margin-top:2rem">Known ARM64 + CUDA 13 limitations</h2>
      <div class="limits-table">
        <div class="limit-row">
          <span class="limit-pkg">open3d</span>
          <span class="limit-status fail">no wheel</span>
          <span class="limit-note">No ARM64 binary. Must build from source (~60 min) or use trimesh instead.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="limit-row">
          <span class="limit-pkg">tensorflow-cpu</span>
          <span class="limit-status fail">no wheel</span>
          <span class="limit-note">No Python 3.12 ARM64 wheel. Use dedicated TF container with Python 3.10.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="limit-row">
          <span class="limit-pkg">vllm</span>
          <span class="limit-status warn">fragile</span>
          <span class="limit-note">No stable cu130 aarch64 release. Pin to specific nightly wheel.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="limit-row">
          <span class="limit-pkg">flash-attn</span>
          <span class="limit-status warn">fragile</span>
          <span class="limit-note">aarch64 builds exist but need TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST=12.0 at build time.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="limit-row">
          <span class="limit-pkg">CUDA 12.x packages</span>
          <span class="limit-status fail">incompatible</span>
          <span class="limit-note">DGX Spark only has libcudart.so.13. Any package built against CUDA 12 will fail with ImportError.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.page-hero { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
.page-hero h1 { margin-top: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
.lead { max-width: 640px; font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.spec-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.4rem; margin-top: 0.75rem; }
.spec-pill {
  font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.72rem;
  padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 100px;
  border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--muted);
  background: var(--panel);
}
.tab-bar { display: flex; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; }
.tab {
  font-size: 0.8rem; padding: 6px 16px; border-radius: 100px;
  border: 1px solid var(--border); cursor: pointer;
  color: var(--muted); background: var(--panel);
  transition: all 0.15s; font-family: var(--font-sans);
}
.tab:hover { color: var(--text); border-color: var(--orange-dark); }
.tab.active { background: var(--orange); color: #fff; border-color: var(--orange); }
.tab-content { display: none; }
.tab-content.active { display: block; }
.tab-desc { color: var(--muted); font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
p { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; }
pre {
  background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 8px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.82rem;
  line-height: 1.8; overflow-x: auto; margin: 0.75rem 0;
  color: var(--text);
}
code {
  font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.82rem;
  background: var(--panel-mid); color: var(--orange-light);
  padding: 2px 7px; border-radius: 4px;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
}
pre code { background: none; border: none; padding: 0; color: var(--text); }
.step { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
.step-header {
  display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}
.step-num {
  width: 24px; height: 24px; border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--orange-tint); border: 1px solid var(--orange-dark);
  color: var(--orange-light); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;
  display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  flex-shrink: 0; font-family: var(--font-mono);
}
.step-title { font-weight: 500; font-size: 0.95rem; }
.badge {
  font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.68rem;
  padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 100px; border: 1px solid;
}
.badge.done { color: var(--orange-light); border-color: var(--orange-dark); background: var(--orange-tint); }
.badge.info { color: #7ab8f0; border-color: #1a4a7a; background: #0d1f35; }
.badge.warn { color: #f0c07a; border-color: #7a5a1a; background: #2a1f0d; }
.badge.planned { color: var(--muted); border-color: var(--border); background: var(--panel); }
.note {
  border-radius: 8px; padding: 8px 14px;
  font-size: 0.8rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); margin: 0.5rem 0;
}
.warn { background: var(--orange-tint); border: 1px solid var(--orange-dark); color: var(--orange-light); }
.info { background: #0d1f35; border: 1px solid #1a4a7a; color: #7ab8f0; }
.pkg-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(180px, 1fr)); gap: 0.6rem; margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem; }
.pkg-card { background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; }
.pkg-name { display: block; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text); font-size: 0.9rem; }
.pkg-ver { display: block; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--orange-light); margin: 2px 0; }
.pkg-note { display: block; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--muted); }
.summary-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
.summary-card { border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem; border: 1px solid var(--border); }
.active-card { background: var(--panel); border-color: var(--orange-dark); }
.planned-card { background: var(--panel); opacity: 0.6; }
.summary-header { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
.summary-name { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--orange-light); }
.summary-card p { font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
.summary-pkgs { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.35rem; }
.summary-size { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 0.75rem; }
.limits-table { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; margin-top: 1rem; }
.limit-row {
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: 160px 90px 1fr;
  gap: 1rem; padding: 8px 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  align-items: start; font-size: 0.85rem;
}
.limit-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.limit-pkg { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text); }
.limit-status { font-size: 0.75rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 100px; border: 1px solid; text-align: center; }
.limit-status.fail { color: #f07a7a; border-color: #7a1a1a; background: #1f0d0d; }
